<title>TURKEY: Turk Akcansa H1 profit jumps.</title>
<headline>Turk Akcansa H1 profit jumps.</headline>
<dateline>ISTANBUL 1997-08-18</dateline>
<text>
<p>Jan-June 1997 final (billion lira unless stated)</p>
<p>				    H1 1997	   H1 1996</p>
<p>				    -------	   -------</p>
<p>    Per share profit (lira)   578.84  vs     129.82</p>
<p>    Net profit		  2,202.47  vs     493.96</p>
<p>    Net sales		  13,278.37  vs   6,572.63</p>
<p>    Operating profit	  3,059.98  vs   1,081.16</p>
<p>    Exceptional income	1,028.47  vs     567.08</p>
<p>    Exceptional expense	193.65   vs     250.34</p>
<p>    Interest paid		626.19   vs   1,110.55</p>
<p>    Total debts		 9,311.09  vs   7,178.08</p>
<p>    Equity		     18,655.35  vs   9,721.17</p>
<p>    Capital		     3,805.16  vs   3,805.16</p>
<p>NOTE - Akcansa Cimento Sanayi ve Ticaret A.S. is Turkey's biggest cement producer, equally owned by Turkish Sabancg conglomerate and Belgian Cimenteries CBR SA, a unit of German Heidelberger Zement. Each partner holds 39.72 percent stake.</p>
<p>The figures above do not take into account Turkey's 78 percent year-on-year consumer price inflation in June.</p>
<p>-- Istanbul newsroom +90-212 275 08 75</p>
